HEADWORD: Outgeneral
<hw>Out*gen"er*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Outgeneraled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or
<conjf>Outgeneralled</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Outgeneraling</conjf> or <conjf>Outgeneralling</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<def>To exceed in generalship; to gain advantage over by superior
military skill or executive ability; to outmaneuver.</def>
<rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

